fit this model and would take up screen real estate.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-tree-widget** (not in search results — likely stale or renamed)\n- Contact management in reme is a flat list of direct contacts. No tree hierarchy is needed.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-checkbox** (`?`)\n- No current or planned feature in reme requires checkbox widgets.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-big-text** (`?`)\n- Large text display. No use case in a messaging client TUI.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-input** (`0.15.0`, headless)\n- A headless input library (no rendering, just input state management). reme uses `tui-textarea` which handles both input state and rendering. `tui-input` would require writing custom rendering code on top.\n- Verdict: **skip**. No benefit over `tui-textarea` for reme's use case.\n\n**tui-slider** (`?`)\n- No use case in reme.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**ratatui-code-editor** (`?`)\n- Code editor with tree-sitter. reme is a messaging app, not a code editor.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n---\n\n### Prioritized adoption recommendation for v0.5\n\n| Priority | Crate | Why now |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `tui-popup` | 6 popups exist or will exist in v0.5. The hand-rolled approach is already duplicating code. |\n| 2 | `throbber-widgets-tui` | v0.5 explicitly requires progress feedback during export/import operations. |\n| 3 | `tui-scrollview` | Message history scrolling is fragile today; adopt before history gets long. |\n| 4 | `ratatui-toaster` | Low priority — assess only if the `app.status` string approach becomes a real UX problem during v0.5. |\n\nThe rest are either redundant with existing deps, wrong UX paradigm for a messaging app, or too immature to take a dependency on.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>46736</total_tokens><tool_uses>14</tool_uses><duration_ms>100959</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/cde6fd4c-88a8-464b-941a-e71717209706/tasks/a3e28562bf7830ef6.output",
