            "content": "## Summary\n\nGeneralize the outbox to support relay entries (opaque envelopes for others) alongside own entries (messages we authored). This enables the node's relay queue without duplicating the delivery state machine.\n\n## Changes\n\n### OutboxOwnership enum\n\n```rust\npub enum OutboxOwnership {\n    Own,   // our message, has inner_bytes + content_id + recipient PublicID\n    Relay, // someone else's message, opaque envelope_bytes only\n}\n```\n\n### New `Relayed` terminal state\n\n```rust\npub enum TieredDeliveryPhase {\n    Urgent,\n    Distributed { confidence, reached_at_ms, last_maintenance_ms },\n    Confirmed { confirmed_at_ms },\n    Relayed { relayed_at_ms: u64 },  // NEW: relay handoff complete\n}\n```\n\n`Relayed` is distinct from `Confirmed` (recipient ACK). Relay entries: Urgent -> Relayed on quorum. Own entries: existing 3-phase flow unchanged.\n\n### OutboxStore trait additions\n\n```rust\nfn outbox_enqueue_relay(\n    &self,\n    routing_key: RoutingKey,\n    message_id: MessageID,\n    envelope_bytes: &[u8],\n    expires_at_ms: Option<u64>,\n    source_target: Option<TargetId>,\n) -> Result<OutboxEntryId, Self::Error>;\n\nfn outbox_get_relay_retry_due(&self, now_ms: u64) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error>;\n```\n\n### PendingMessage changes\n\n- `recipient: Option<PublicID>` (None for relay)\n- `routing_key: RoutingKey` (always set)\n- `content_id: Option<ContentId>` (None for relay)\n- `ownership: OutboxOwnership`\n- `source_target: Option<TargetId>` (loop prevention)\n\n### Schema migration\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE outbox_entries ADD COLUMN ownership INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;\nALTER TABLE outbox_entries ADD COLUMN routing_key BLOB;\nALTER TABLE outbox_entries ADD COLUMN source_target TEXT;\n\nCREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_outbox_relay_dedup\n    ON outbox_entries(routing_key, message_id) WHERE ownership = 1;\n```\n\nNULLable `recipient` and `content_id` for relay entries (not zero-byte sentinels).\n\n### Ownership-conditional behavior\n\n| Method | Own | Relay |\n|---|---|---|\n| `outbox_get_by_content_id()` | Works | Never called (content_id is None) |\n| `outbox_get_for_recipient()` | Works | N/A (use routing_key) |\n| `outbox_get_maintenance_due()` | Returns Distributed entries | Skips relay entries |\n| `outbox_mark_confirmed()` | Sets Confirmed | Sets Relayed |\n\n### Relay-specific behavior\n\n- Deduplication on `(routing_key, message_id)` via unique index\n- Backpressure: configurable `max_relay_entries` + `max_relay_bytes`\n- TTL: `min(envelope.ttl_hours, relay_max_ttl)`. `None` defaults to `relay_max_ttl`\n- Loop prevention: `source_target` excluded from egress\n- Cleanup: `Relayed` entries cleaned up with shorter retention than `Confirmed`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Schema migration adds new columns without breaking existing data\n- Own entries work exactly as before (all existing tests pass)\n- Relay entries can be enqueued, queried, transitioned to Relayed, cleaned up\n- Dedup index prevents duplicate relay entries\n- Mixed Own + Relay entries coexist without interference\n\n## Requirements\n\n- #179 — TrustLevel + Contact rework (routing_key column in contacts)\n",
