            "content": "## Summary\n\nImplement relay queue ingress: the HTTP submit handler in Personal Relay mode accepts envelopes, applies trust-based policy, and enqueues qualifying envelopes in the relay outbox.\n\n## Changes to POST /api/v1/submit\n\nCurrently (`apps/node/src/api.rs:528`): envelope is stored in mailbox and replicated fire-and-forget.\n\nIn Personal Relay mode, after mailbox storage:\n1. Resolve submitter's TrustLevel (signed header -> contact lookup, or Stranger)\n2. Check `relay_for` threshold\n3. Check backpressure limits (`max_relay_entries`, `max_relay_bytes`)\n4. `DeliveryEngine::enqueue_relay()` with `source_target` for loop prevention\n\n### HTTP response change\n\nCurrent response: `{ \"results\": [...] }` per frame.\n\nNew response adds relay status per frame:\n```json\n{\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"status\": \"ok\", \"relayed\": true },\n    { \"status\": \"ok\", \"relayed\": false, \"relay_reason\": \"policy\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nMailbox storage and relay are independent. Mailbox always stores (if `accept_from` passes). Relay failure does not fail the submit.\n\n### Trust resolution at submit time\n\n| Scenario | TrustLevel |\n|---|---|\n| Anonymous POST | Stranger |\n| Signed `x-node-signature` with known PublicID | Contact's TrustLevel |\n| Signed with unknown PublicID | Stranger |\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Personal Relay mode enqueues qualifying envelopes in relay outbox\n- Infrastructure mode is unchanged (no relay enqueue)\n- Stranger submissions are not relayed (default policy `relay_for = verified+`)\n- Verified contact submissions are relayed\n- Queue-full does not fail mailbox storage\n- Response body indicates relay status per frame\n- Source target is recorded for loop prevention\n\n## Requirements\n\n- #23 — Node operating modes (mode toggle)\n- Outbox generalization issue (outbox_enqueue_relay)\n- #75 — Peer capability policy (RelayPolicy)\n",
