            "content": "## Summary\n\nImplement relay queue egress: the DeliveryEngine tick loop processes relay entries and delivers them to configured Quorum targets (HTTP mailboxes, MQTT brokers).\n\n## Implementation\n\nThe `DeliveryEngine::tick()` method already handles urgent retries and maintenance for Own entries. For v0.6:\n\n1. `outbox_get_relay_retry_due()` returns relay entries in Urgent phase due for retry\n2. For each relay entry: `TransportCoordinator::submit_tiered()` with Quorum targets only\n   - Exclude `source_target` from target set (loop prevention)\n   - No Direct tier (node has no active peer discovery in v0.6)\n3. Record delivery result: quorum reached -> transition to `Relayed`\n4. TTL expiry: relay entries past TTL -> `Expired`\n5. Cleanup: `Relayed` entries deleted after short delay (configurable, default 5min)\n\n### v0.6 constraint: Quorum-only\n\nThe node does not do active peer discovery in v0.6 (DiscoveryController stays in client). Relay egress uses only configured stable Quorum targets. Direct-tier relay from nodes is deferred to v0.7.\n\n### Intermittent connectivity\n\nPhase 1 retry loop with exponential backoff (5s -> 300s cap) handles offline periods naturally. When Internet returns, queued relay entries are delivered.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Relay entries are forwarded to configured Quorum targets\n- Source target is excluded from egress (no echo)\n- Quorum reached -> entry transitions to Relayed\n- TTL expired -> entry transitions to Expired\n- Relayed entries are cleaned up after delay\n- Retry with backoff works during intermittent connectivity\n- No Direct-tier delivery from node in v0.6\n\n## Requirements\n\n- #23 — Node operating modes (DeliveryEngine runs in Personal Relay mode)\n- Outbox generalization issue (Relayed state, relay queries)\n- #75 — Peer capability policy (relay_for threshold)\n",
